        {
            "title": "MyToolBox - Safe food and feed through an integrated ToolBox for mycotoxin management",
            "date": {
                "start": {
                    "month": 3,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2016
                },
                "end": {
                    "month": 2,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2020
                }
            },
            "description": "MyToolBox forecasting tool helps growers' decision making during the growing season of winter wheat, durum wheat, barley and maize to minimize to DON contamination risks and potential economic loss. This tool uses local weather data and the agricultural management practices for the specific fields to compute the risk of mycotoxin contamination at harvest. \n\nAs one of the MytoolBox e-platform core development team members, my tasks include pre-harvest mycotoxin prediction model development, front-end general design and coordination. ",
